A4.text: Theodore Roosevelt was the youngest person to become U.S. president at age 42, who succeeded to the office after the assassination of William McKinley.

A5.text: John F. Kennedy was the youngest person elected as president, at age 43

A6.text: At the age of 46, Grant was the youngest president yet elected.
